{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.12",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 12",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 12 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:2",
      "text": "“No doubt, but you are the people, and wisdom will die with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:3",
      "text": "But I have understanding as well as you; I am not inferior to you. Yes, who doesn’t know such things as these?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:4",
      "text": "I am like one who is a joke to his neighbor, I, who called on God, and he answered. The just, the blameless man is a joke.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:5",
      "text": "In the thought of him who is at ease there is contempt for misfortune. It is ready for them whose foot slips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:6",
      "text": "The tents of robbers prosper. Those who provoke God are secure, who carry their god in their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:7",
      "text": "“But ask the animals now, and they will teach you; the birds of the sky, and they will tell you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:8",
      "text": "Or speak to the earth, and it will teach you. The fish of the sea will declare to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:9",
      "text": "Who doesn’t know that in all these, Yahweh’s hand has done this,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:10",
      "text": "in whose hand is the life of every living thing, and the breath of all mankind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:11",
      "text": "Doesn’t the ear try words, even as the palate tastes its food?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:12",
      "text": "With aged men is wisdom, in length of days understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:13",
      "text": "“With God is wisdom and might. He has counsel and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:14",
      "text": "Behold, he breaks down, and it can’t be built again. He imprisons a man, and there can be no release.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:15",
      "text": "Behold, he withholds the waters, and they dry up. Again, he sends them out, and they overturn the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:16",
      "text": "With him is strength and wisdom. The deceived and the deceiver are his.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:17",
      "text": "He leads counselors away stripped. He makes judges fools.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:18",
      "text": "He loosens the bond of kings. He binds their waist with a belt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:19",
      "text": "He leads priests away stripped, and overthrows the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:20",
      "text": "He removes the speech of those who are trusted, and takes away the understanding of the elders.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:21",
      "text": "He pours contempt on princes, and loosens the belt of the strong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:22",
      "text": "He uncovers deep things out of darkness, and brings out to light the shadow of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:23",
      "text": "He increases the nations, and he destroys them. He enlarges the nations, and he leads them captive.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:24",
      "text": "He takes away understanding from the chiefs of the people of the earth, and causes them to wander in a wilderness where there is no way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.12.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 12:25",
      "text": "They grope in the dark without light. He makes them stagger like a drunken man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
